Runtime
===============================================================================

1. Runtime
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The runtime loads source, resolves modules, evaluates programs, manages host contexts, and reports events.

2. Host
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

A host embeds or launches the runtime and provides resource providers. Browser and CLI behavior is documented under `hosts/browser/docs` and `hosts/cli/docs`.

3. Source resolver
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The source resolver maps source imports such as `+> ./geometry.mec` to source text and module records.

4. Module record
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

A module record contains a resolved module identity, imports, exports, private bindings, and evaluation state.

5. Module version
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

A module version identifies the loaded module content or provider version used to satisfy imports.

6. Context
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

A context is a host-backed resource root bound to an `@name`. Contexts are imported from manifests or declared directly by advanced resource syntax.

7. Resource provider
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

A resource provider implements reads, writes, and sends for a context base URI.

8. Capability grant
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

A capability grant authorizes an operation on a scoped resource path.

9. Runtime event
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Runtime events describe load, validation, evaluation, resource, and diagnostic activity.

10. Workspace
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

A workspace is the configured set of source roots, module roots, config files, and host projections used for a run.

11. Execution boundary
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The execution boundary separates Mech evaluation from host effects. Host effects cross this boundary through resource providers and capability checks.
